<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> The <a href="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutspelling/castorsugar?view=uk" class="external text" title="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutspelling/castorsugar?view=uk" rel="nofollow">Oxford</a> English Dictionary (<a href="/wiki/Oxford_English_Dictionary" title="Oxford English Dictionary">OED</a>) classifies both spellings as correct, but "castor" used to prevail.</li>
